Synchronoss Technologies, Inc. Announces Addition Of SmartMobility™ Product To ConvergenceNow® Plus+™






Business Wire




May 3, 2011 4:01 PM EDT













 


















































  Synchronoss Technologies, Inc. (NASDAQ: SNCR), the world’s leading provider of transaction management, cloud enablement and connectivity services for connected devices, today announced that it has enhanced its ConvergenceNow ®Plus +™ platform with the addition of the SmartMobility™ product.  The SmartMobility product will drive faster and more efficient device connectivity from the cloud. As a result, we believe that SmartMobility will revolutionize device activation, connectivity and management for connected devices across networks. Synchronoss also announced the acquisition of privately held Sapience Knowledge Systems, which brings significant domain expertise and will help to accelerate Synchronoss’ time to market with its new mobility management product.  Stephen G. Waldis, President and Chief Executive Officer of Synchronoss, said, “With the introduction of SmartMobility, Synchronoss is continuing the expansion of its ConvergenceNow Plus+ platform for enabling transaction management via the cloud directly from the device itself. Estimates for connected device adoption are reaching the billions of unit levels, and these devices will increasingly be running on multiple networks. As a result, the industry needs a more integrated solution to combine activation and synch technology with smarter connectivity, in addition to moving away from standalone software that needs to be installed and tested. The integration of SmartMobility with our ConvergenceNow Plus + platform creates a standardized way to service the industry, which benefits both enterprises and consumers by eliminating redundancies, reducing costs and streamlining faster product introductions.”  Waldis added, “We are partnering with a Tier One Service Provider as well as some Original Equipment Manufacturers (OEMs) to roll out our SmartMobility product. We currently anticipate moving into production in late 2011 with additional functionality and partners being launched in 2012.”  “We are very excited to be a part of the Synchronoss family,” said Biju Nair, President & CEO of Sapience. “The addition of SmartMobility to Synchronoss’ ConvergenceNow Plus+ platform creates a new paradigm in mobility management that cost-effectively improves time-to-market and enables new revenue streams for our customers.”  



 








 










































